  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study will compare the two methods 5 days holtermonitoring and 30 days thumb
      electrocardiogram for detection of atrial fibrillation in stroke patients
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Patients with a newly stroke will be examined with both 5 day holter monitoring and 30 days
      thumb ECG at the same time. The detection rates of the two methods will be compared
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
